2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 37
BY REPRESENTATIVE WILEY
MILITARY AFFAIRS: Memorializes Congress to issue the Armed Forces Expeditionary
Medal to U.S. veterans who served in Honduras from 1981 to 1992
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To memorialize the United States Congress to take such actions as are necessary to issue the
3 Armed Forces Expeditionary Medal to U.S. veterans who served in Honduras from
4 1981 to 1992.
5 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has
6 consistently demonstrated its belief that military members and veterans who serve or have
7 served in hostile environments should be recognized; and
8 WHEREAS, the U.S. military maintained a presence in Honduras throughout the
9 1980s and 1990s, providing training and conducting military exercises with the host nation;
10 and
11 WHEREAS, the presence of U.S. troops served as a deterrent to aggression in the
12 region and as a means of support for democratic values through civil action in Honduran
13 communities; and
14 WHEREAS, U.S. troops were equipped with live ammunition and assisted the
15 Honduran military in training and combat support; and
16 WHEREAS, U.S. troops in Honduras experienced hostile fire and imminent danger;
17 and
18 WHEREAS, at least one U.S. service member received a Purple Heart because of
19 terrorist activity in Honduras; and
20 WHEREAS, U.S. troops lost their lives while in Honduras due to terrorist activity
21 and hazardous circumstances.
